documentation.text: @dev Used to deposit NFTs into a pair after creation and emit an event for indexing (if recipient is indeed a pair)
@dev Used to deposit ERC20s into a pair after creation and emit an event for indexing (if recipient is indeed an ERC20 pair and the token matches)

params._assetRecipient: The address that will receive the assets traders give during trades. If set to address(0), assets will be sent to the pool address. Not available to TRADE pools.
params._bondingCurve: The bonding curve for the pair to price NFTs, must be whitelisted
params._delta: The delta value used by the bonding curve. The meaning of delta depends on the specific curve.
params._fee: The fee taken by the LP in each trade. Can only be non-zero if _poolType is Trade.
params._initialNFTIDs: The list of IDs of NFTs to transfer from the sender to the pair
params._nft: The NFT contract of the collection the pair trades

depositERC20(address,address,uint256).details: Used to deposit ERC20s into a pair after creation and emit an event for indexing (if recipient is indeed an ERC20 pair and the token matches)

params.variant: The pair variant (NFT is enumerable or not, pair uses ETH or ERC20)

returns._0: True if the address is the specified pair variant, false otherwise
